The man who is sweeping country music awards right now is being taken to court by a wedding band based in Pennsylvania called Jelly Roll. Band member Kurt said the solo singer Jelly Roll is infringing on the group's trademark. He is seeking an injunction and wants Jelly Roll to stop going by Jelly Roll. The band started using the name in the 80s, before Jason Bradley Deford was born. They trademarked the name in 2010 and renewed again in 2019. Jelly Roll, a singer, has talked about how his mom gave him this nickname as a child, but he started using it around 2010 for music distribution purposes. They indicate in the lawsuit, the prior to Jelly Roll Singer success, if you Google them, you could. Now that he has risen to fame, you have to work much harder to find them. So they sent a cease and desist letter to Jelly Roll, whose team was like, let's discuss this. And basically his team said, listen, are you actually competition here? What? The way that that is so ferocious and accurate all at the same time. I cannot. So Jelly No Space Roll is saying that Jelly Space Roll is getting ready to go on a national tour, which just happened to go through Philadelphia. Whoo! A territory war is Even marketing it with the name Jelly Roll. They say that Jelly Rolls unapologetic infringement is causing confusion because we made mistake them. What? His lawsuit is honestly very dramatic, and I love it. In conclusion, the band feels like Jelly Roll is creating unfair competition, and they would like him to find a new name again. I would just argue no one is confused here. Literally no one. But now we wait for a response. Stay tuned.

voice_to_text: Breaking news they have now revealed the cause of death for the boy who has found a sea set trails Carolina Youth Camp. Trails Carolina is a camp for troubled youth. The victim in this case was sent there by his parents. As you may recall, back in February, the boy was found deceased by one of the camp counselors. They said he was located after a round of wellness checks were performed throughout the evening. Now officials say that the boy most likely passed due to suffocation. In the report it asked one of the staff members if they believe the child suffocated and they said quote, yes. The boy was told to sleep in a Bibby or a small single person tent. This was inside of the cabin at the camp. The Bibby of the zipper apparently broke off and the staff member used the zip tie to enclose the tent instead. That staff member told authorities that they believe that quote, he and the camp were responsible for the boys passing. When the staff member was asked what they could have done differently, they said that quote, I could have opened the boys tent and repositioned him. Staff members were supposed to check on campers at midnight, 3:00am and 6:00am. And around 3:00am on February 3rd, staff members said that they heard heavy breathing and quote mumbling coming from the boy's baby. However, they did nothing. The same staff member did a check around 6:00am and said that The boy was still breathing at 6:00am. The staff member did a check on the boy and said that he was certain he heard breathing, but said the boy was quote, no longer heavily breathing. Law enforcement was dispatched to the camp around 8:00am when the boy was found unresponsive. The staff member said, quote, my actions that night was to perform night checks. That was my responsibility, which I failed on. I do feel like the baby had a lot to do with it. Suffocation is always a possibility when equipment is used wrong. The trails Carolina Camp regularly made new campers sleep in the bivy with alarms on the zippers when they first arrived at the camp until they are deemed safe enough to sleep outside of it. The camp's director said that they were not aware that the camp was using this practice. To save to date on this case, make sure you click the playlist below. I'll keep you guys updated. voice_to_text: Thanks to a deathbed confession, a nearly 24 year old cold case was closed this week when the bodies of a missing girl and her mother were found. Ten year old Natasha Alex Carter and her mother Susan disappeared from their home in Beckley, West Virginia in August 2000. But at first police initially reported that Alex may have been abducted by her mother. In a press release from December 2021 about the case, the FBI Pittsburgh said quote at the time of their disappearance, Susan Carter and Alex's father were having a custody dispute and Alex moved in with her mother and mother's new husband, which it's not confirmed that it was actually her mother's new husband, but they moved in and then not long after that, Susan and Alex disappeared. But while it was initially suspected as a parental abduction by Susan after the two remained missing, an investigation into other possibilities ensued, but unfortunately the case went cold. In 2021, the FBI reopened the cold case and started looking into the man Susan and Alex were living with, Larry Webb, which is of his home. Were done in 2022 and 2023 and they found a bullet embedded in the wall of what was Alex's bedroom. Bullet was tested for DNA and it confirmed that blood on it belonged to Alex. In October 2023, Larry Webb was indicted on first degree murder charges for Alex's death, despite Alex and Susan's bodies never being found due to his deteriorating health. Though Webb was Not arrested until April 12th, 2024, but since then he was being held without bond. On Monday he had a medical episode, after which, in a quote, come to Jesus moment on his deathbed, he confessed to authorities what he had done. Upclaimed that on August 8th, 2000, he had gotten into an argument with Susan over money. He said he was missing some cash and believed that she had taken it and spent it. The argument escalated and he shot her, and then he ended up shooting Alex so there would be no witnesses. Webb then wrapped their bodies in bed linens and placed them in the basement that night. Over the next two nights, he dug a shallow grave in the woods on his property, eventually burying them in his clothes and then walking free for the next 20 years. On April 22nd, 2024, Larry Webb died at Mount Olive Correctional Complex, and six hours later, Susan and Alex's remains were found at his property in Beckley. Fortunately, now that Webb is dead, he cannot be charged in connection to their deaths. At least now they have been found and can be properly laid to rest. Alex's father, Rick Lafferty, said after the discovery, quote, it's kind of a sad day, but also a happy day because I can bring my baby home. Rest in peace, Alex and Susan.

Thirty nine year old Sergio was an average guy and he was on vacation at a resort in Brazil called the Kenoa Cabrata Resort. On that day, Sergio decided he wanted to make use of the zipline that was on property. After all, it looked like a beautiful, fun thing to go do, he had no idea that a part of the zipline support structure was weak. And tragically, Sergio heading down the zipline was a straw that broke the camel. Or ziplines. Back in the video, Sergio can be seen smiling, hollering and enjoying his last moments on earth before suddenly the zipline collapses and he plummets to his death. This is an actual picture of local investigators checking out the collapse support beam. After this incident, officials in the local city banned all ziplines for the moment and eventually the 35 year old owner of the zipline company was charged with manslaughter in Sergio's death.
